<div id="review_3728443734" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3728443734" />
    <a title="Jonathan" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/1959589-jonathan"><img alt="Jonathan" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1624589216p2/1959589.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3728443734?book_show_action=true">Jul 20, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Jonathan" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Jonathan" href="/user/show/1959589-jonathan">Jonathan</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback " href="/book/show/29430670-wizard-and-glass">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1959589-jonathan?shelf=fantasy">fantasy</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1959589-jonathan?shelf=science-fiction">science-fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1959589-jonathan?shelf=horror">horror</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3728443734" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer15106937645255405343"><b>
  <i>“If it&apos;s ka, it&apos;ll come like a wind, and your plans will stand before it no more than a barn before a cyclone”</i>
</b><br/><br/>The amount of time it took me to finish this volume should not be held against the work itself but Ka. This volume took much longer to read than anticipated, from being chosen just 3 months into a new position to train all departmental new hires to shifts in one&apos;s home life. <br/><br/>On the whole, it is easy to see why this volume is so polarizing amongst the fandom. On the one hand, it does </span>
  <span id="freeText15106937645255405343" style="display:none"><b>
  <i>“If it's ka, it'll come like a wind, and your plans will stand before it no more than a barn before a cyclone”</i>
</b><br /><br />The amount of time it took me to finish this volume should not be held against the work itself but Ka. This volume took much longer to read than anticipated, from being chosen just 3 months into a new position to train all departmental new hires to shifts in one's home life. <br /><br />On the whole, it is easy to see why this volume is so polarizing amongst the fandom. On the one hand, it does very little to further our ka-tet towards the Dark Tower. On the other, it gives Roland an unforgettable air of realism and background. It was essential to the story and the world, even if it did lack some of the urgency of the previous volumes. <br /><br />It, however, also introduced some incredibly engaging characters; some I was despondent to see go, and others I was cheering from the mortal coil. <br /><br />This was, much like the book has our ka-tet doing, a slower ambling exploration of a walk, and I'm ok with that. <br /><br /><b>
  <i>“Stand and be true”</i>
</b> Roland and company, until we meet again.</span>
  <a data-text-id="15106937645255405343" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


